article.headline: Samford 64, IUPUI 50
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Akeem Clark scored 19 points and three of his teammates scored in the double digits to lead IUPUI to a 64-50 victory over Samford on Tuesday. James Booyer scored 14 points for the Jaguars, while Brandon Cole put up 13 including 3 three-pointers. George Hill added 11. IUPUI led at half time 28-25. J. Robert Merritt scored 15 points to lead the Bulldogs. Samford had a higher shooting percentage for field goal shots -- 53.1 percent compared to 42.3 percent for IUPUI -- but the Jaguars got off more shots. Samford made 17-of-32 field goals, compared to 22-of-52 for IUPUI.
